64
00:06:03,128 --> 00:06:06,120
It's a girl. It's a girl.

65
00:06:46,671 --> 00:06:47,899
Hey.

66
00:06:54,246 --> 00:06:56,180
I'm sorry, doctor.

67
00:07:09,094 --> 00:07:12,791
All right. Clean her up, please.
But keep her in the other room.

68
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:16,430
I don't want my wife to know yet.

69
00:07:24,042 --> 00:07:26,977
- David.
- Sleep now, sweetheart.

70
00:07:27,913 --> 00:07:30,609
You were incredible.

71
00:07:36,488 --> 00:07:38,786
You're a beauty.

72
00:08:01,847 --> 00:08:06,807
There's a home outside Louisville.
I want you to take her there.

73
00:08:07,686 --> 00:08:11,053
She's a mongoloid.
She won't live long.

74
00:08:11,556 --> 00:08:13,217
- Caroline.
- But, why?

75
00:08:17,896 --> 00:08:22,595
My sister died when she was 12.
It destroyed my mother's life.

76
00:08:27,439 --> 00:08:29,566
I can't do that to Norah.

77
00:08:58,103 --> 00:09:03,040
Here. It's just off the highway,
about 60 miles.

78
00:09:04,376 --> 00:09:05,809
I'll call ahead.

79
00:09:10,949 --> 00:09:12,576
I can't thank you enough.

80
00:09:34,906 --> 00:09:38,034
<i>Unfortunately, the blizzard will be</i>
<i>continuing throughout the night.</i>

