Stop it. Stop it.

87
00:11:24,449 --> 00:11:26,679
Well, don't just stand there.
Give me a hand.

88
00:11:26,851 --> 00:11:29,581
Billy, stop it. Stop it.

89
00:11:29,754 --> 00:11:32,848
Hold him down.
Now, get me the strap.

90
00:11:34,192 --> 00:11:37,787
Oh, stop it. Calm down, Billy.
Hold this down.

91
00:11:37,962 --> 00:11:41,090
- Are you the new nurse?
- No, I'm here to...

92
00:11:41,266 --> 00:11:43,257
- Did Dr. Henry call?
- Who?

93
00:11:43,435 --> 00:11:45,926
A doctor was supposed to call ahead.
He sent me...

94
00:11:46,104 --> 00:11:48,402
We're short-staffed tonight.
Hold his legs down.

95
00:11:48,573 --> 00:11:50,473
If anybody called,
I didn't hear about it.

96
00:11:50,642 --> 00:11:54,339
Billy, if you don't settle down, you're
gonna be in these all day tomorrow.

97
00:11:54,512 --> 00:11:56,980
Do you understand me?
What was that name again?

98
00:11:57,515 --> 00:12:01,747
- Dr. Henry.
- Okay, wait here. Let me ask Janet.

99
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:38,951
You better hurry up.
We're closed in 10 minutes.

100
00:12:47,232 --> 00:12:49,063
Come on.

101
00:12:55,240 --> 00:13:00,507
Here we go. Come on, little girl.
That's it. Good girl.

102
00:13:01,546 --> 00:13:03,036
Good, good girl.

103
00:13:18,363 --> 00:13:22,060
Oh, God. Oh, God.

104
00:13:25,103 --> 00:13:26,536
Oh, God.

105
00:13:31,342 --> 00:13:32,570
Wait, come back.

106
00:13:34,245 --> 00:13:35,906
I have a baby here!

107
00:13:47,225 --> 00:13:49,625
I have a baby here.

108
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:58,098
- Hi.
- Hey.

109
00:14:03,541 --> 00:14:05,873
- Hi.
- You were so brave.

110
00:14:15,620 --> 00:14:16,712
Look at him.

111
00:14:18,156 --> 00:14:20,590
Our beautiful boy, our perf...

112
00:14:21,459 --> 00:14:23,256
Perfect Paul.

113
00:14:33,338 --> 00:14:35,238
What? What is it?

114
00:14:40,445 --> 00:14:42,436
We had twins, honey.

115
00:14:43,147 --> 00:14:44,944
One of each.

116
00:14:47,185 --> 00:14:48,812
Twins?

117
00:14:51,489 --> 00:14:53,616
Where is she?

118
00:14:58,596 --> 00:15:00,257
You know I love you, right?

119
00:15:01,032 --> 00:15:02,556
Right?

120
00:15:03,968 --> 00:15:06,129
Oh, God.

121
00:15:09,307 --> 00:15:11,969
I am so sorry.

122
00:15:19,017 --> 00:15:22,077
She died as she was born.

123
00:15:43,675 --> 00:15:45,973
Did you forget something?

124
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:54,848
I was trying to get to the phone.
I'm out of gas.

125
00:15:56,321 --> 00:15:57,720
Out of gas?

126
00:15:58,456 --> 00:16:03,052
Listen, lady, at this time,
in this weather, you're also out of luck.

127
00:16:06,664 --> 00:16:08,188
Oh, man.

128
00:16:10,401 --> 00:16:13,837
- How old?
- Newborn.

129
00:16:14,605 --> 00:16:17,335
Listen, you gotta
come join me in my rig.

130
00:16:21,045 --> 00:16:24,242
I delivered a load of milk.
I'm just waiting out the storm.

131
00:16:26,818 --> 00:16:29,582
Lady, I'm considering that baby.

132
00:17:00,118 --> 00:17:01,551
Name's Al.

133
00:17:04,422 --> 00:17:05,616
Al Simpson.

134
00:17:06,090 --> 00:17:07,751
Caroline Gill.

135
00:17:11,095 --> 00:17:13,120
Oh, I bet you have a story.

136
00:17:17,168 --> 00:17:18,567
Where were you two headed?

137
00:17:19,537 --> 00:17:21,698
- Lexington.
- Lexington?

138
00:17:21,873 --> 00:17:24,740
Well, if it's only Lexington,
I can give you a lift.

139
00:17:26,911 --> 00:17:30,074
I might as well park the rig there
as here.

140
00:17:30,748 --> 00:17:33,717
- If it doesn't put you out.
- Oh, hell, no. It's...

141
00:17:34,652 --> 00:17:36,051
Oh, pardon my French.

142
00:17:38,489 --> 00:17:41,549
I mean, Lexington is on my way.

143
00:17:44,629 --> 00:17:45,653
Thank you.

144
00:18:21,132 --> 00:18:22,759
He is perfect, isn't he?

145
00:18:31,209 --> 00:18:33,143
I wanna see her.

146
00:18:34,445 --> 00:18:40,247
- Oh, no.
- Just for a moment, David. Please.

147
00:18:42,153 --> 00:18:44,314
They took her away.

148
00:18:53,030 --> 00:18:55,157
No.

149
00:19:28,966 --> 00:19:30,991
Morning.

150
00:19:31,469 --> 00:19:34,495
Oh, hi. I hope you...

151
00:19:34,672 --> 00:19:38,335
I hope you don't mind.
I made myself at home.

152
00:19:39,377 --> 00:19:42,676
No, it smells good. I'm hungry.

153
00:19:42,847 --> 00:19:47,147
That's great because,
you know, I made lots.

154
00:19:49,353 --> 00:19:52,379
- Thanks.
- I talked to a friend of mine.

155
00:19:52,557 --> 00:19:57,051
And he's gonna fill your car with gas
and then drop it off this afternoon.

156
00:19:57,228 --> 00:19:59,321
Why, that's incredibly kind.

157
00:19:59,497 --> 00:20:01,260
Yeah.
It's my infinite pleasure, ma'am.

158
00:20:01,432 --> 00:20:03,400
- Thank you.
- There you go.

159
00:20:04,135 --> 00:20:07,263
Well, listen,
I've been meaning to say...

160
00:20:07,438 --> 00:20:11,431
...that I'm sorry for whatever happened
with your little girl's...

161
00:20:11,609 --> 00:20:14,772
- Well, you know, her father.
- Thank you.

162
00:20:14,946 --> 00:20:17,938
I know for a fact
how bad men can behave.

163
00:20:18,115 --> 00:20:20,481
I used to behave
a little bad myself sometimes.

164
00:20:22,753 --> 00:20:24,050
I doubt that.

165
00:20:26,891 --> 00:20:31,453
Anyway, I gotta...
I'm heading back to Pittsburgh.

166
00:20:31,629 --> 00:20:35,429
It's my home between runs, so...
You know Pittsburgh?

167
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,534
- No.
- Oh, it's a great town.

168
00:20:37,702 --> 00:20:39,863
It's great. You'll...

169
00:20:40,671 --> 00:20:42,662
You should come visit sometime.

170
00:20:46,744 --> 00:20:51,579
Anyway, if you do... Let me...
Let me give you my phone number.

171
00:20:52,650 --> 00:20:54,481
You know, just in case you visit...

172
00:20:55,653 --> 00:20:58,281
...or, you know,
you just wanna talk sometime.

173
00:21:01,492 --> 00:21:03,483
I'm a pretty good listener.

174
00:21:04,562 --> 00:21:06,291
I know that.

175
00:21:11,435 --> 00:21:13,266
Thank you.

176
00:21:34,358 --> 00:21:36,690
- Lexington East Clinic.
- <i>Hi, Ruby, it's Caroline.</i>

177
00:21:37,928 --> 00:21:41,295
I won't be coming in this afternoon.
I'm coming down with something.

178
00:21:41,465 --> 00:21:44,992
Don't worry. I'll call in Emma.
Hey, did you hear?

179
00:21:45,169 --> 00:21:48,900
Dr. Henry's wife gave birth
to a baby boy last night.

180
00:21:49,740 --> 00:21:51,139
And a little girl who died.

181
00:21:53,144 --> 00:21:55,544
- She died?
- <i>Yes.</i>

182
00:21:55,713 --> 00:21:57,010
Yes, isn't that awful?

183
00:22:12,330 --> 00:22:15,231
- Hi, Kay.
- David, honey, I'm so sorry.

184
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:18,429
We all just rushed over
as soon as we heard.

185
00:22:19,503 --> 00:22:20,527
Thank you.

186
00:22:20,705 --> 00:22:24,505
I just want you to know
that we'll all be there on Tuesday.

187
00:22:25,176 --> 00:22:27,974
- What do you mean, "Tuesday"?
- We...

188
00:22:28,145 --> 00:22:31,945
We all talked her into it.
We think it's the best thing.

189
00:22:32,917 --> 00:22:35,249
- A memorial?
- Something small.

190
00:22:35,419 --> 00:22:38,047
Something simple.
It'll help us put her to rest.

191
00:22:38,222 --> 00:22:41,214
Norah, I don't think we need
a public ceremony to do that.

192
00:22:41,392 --> 00:22:44,589
- She died, there's no shame in that.
- No, of course not.

193
00:22:44,762 --> 00:22:46,923
We need to mark
her presence here on earth.

194
00:22:47,098 --> 00:22:50,033
Whose idea is this?
Your little sewing circle?

195
00:22:50,701 --> 00:22:53,192
Everyone agrees
it's the right thing to do.

196
00:22:53,371 --> 00:22:55,999
Kay called the papers and the church.
It's been arranged.

197
00:22:56,173 --> 00:22:58,403
Why didn't Kay call me?
Why didn't you ask me?

198
00:22:58,576 --> 00:23:00,771
This isn't wrong.
You think this is wrong?

199
00:23:00,945 --> 00:23:03,573
- No, Norah...
- You touched her.

200
00:23:03,748 --> 00:23:06,239
You held her. At least you held her.

201
00:23:12,423 --> 00:23:14,152
- Oh, God.
- Caroline.

202
00:23:14,325 --> 00:23:15,917
You told her she died?

203
00:23:16,594 --> 00:23:18,619
Well, I tried to tell her the truth,
but...

204
00:23:18,796 --> 00:23:22,061
I know what it's like to grow up
in a house with a terminally-ill child.

205
00:23:22,233 --> 00:23:25,430
Any joy my mother had in life,
disappeared when my sister was born.

206
00:23:25,603 --> 00:23:29,130
Phoebe only has half a brain.
She'll wind up in a home eventually.

207
00:23:29,306 --> 00:23:31,740
No one raises mongoloids
on their own.

208
00:23:31,909 --> 00:23:34,605
And why do I need
to tell Norah any of this...

209
00:23:34,779 --> 00:23:36,644
...if it's just gonna break her heart?

210
00:23:36,814 --> 00:23:38,509
You mean it's not broken now?

211
00:23:40,384 --> 00:23:44,912
She didn't see the baby.
Someday she'll recover. God willing.

212
00:23:45,089 --> 00:23:48,581
And she never will, knowing
that her daughter's dying in an insti...

213
00:23:54,632 --> 00:23:56,259
I couldn't leave her in that place.

214
00:23:56,434 --> 00:23:58,834
Well, why not?
Why in the world not?

215
00:23:59,003 --> 00:24:00,300
Have you been there?

216
00:24:01,038 --> 00:24:03,097
Oh, God.

217
00:24:09,346 --> 00:24:15,376
Look, do whatever you have to do.
Find a better place for her if you can.

218
00:24:16,954 --> 00:24:19,218
I have the birth certificate.
It's not filled out.

219
00:24:21,492 --> 00:24:23,619
- Take this.
- I don't want your money.

220
00:24:23,794 --> 00:24:25,056
It's not for you.

221
00:24:25,229 --> 00:24:28,096
Just please, don't tell Norah.
Please don't.

222
00:24:28,265 --> 00:24:29,698
Don't you wanna see her?

223
00:24:30,601 --> 00:24:33,331
The first goodbye was hard enough.

224
00:24:36,674 --> 00:24:39,905
<i>Though little Phoebe's body</i>
<i>rests elsewhere...</i>

225
00:24:40,077 --> 00:24:42,875
...we erect a stone here,
in her memory.

226
00:24:44,315 --> 00:24:46,215
The night is as clear as day.

227
00:24:47,585 --> 00:24:50,850
The darkness and the light
are to thee both alike.

228
00:24:52,723 --> 00:24:55,749
Thou has set our misdeeds
before thee...

229
00:24:55,926 --> 00:25:00,989
...and our secret sins
in the light of thy countenance.

230
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:06,436
For the things that are seen
are transient.

231
00:25:06,604 --> 00:25:10,370
But the things that are unseen
are eternal.

232
00:25:10,875 --> 00:25:13,207
We have committed her body
to the elements.

233
00:25:13,377 --> 00:25:14,901
Earth to earth...

234
00:25:15,346 --> 00:25:18,281
...ashes to ashes, dust to dust.

235
00:25:18,449 --> 00:25:21,043
The Lord keep her and bless her.

236
00:25:21,218 --> 00:25:24,381
The Lord make his face
to shine upon her...

237
00:25:25,823 --> 00:25:28,121
...and give her peace.

238
00:25:35,766 --> 00:25:37,199
Amen.

239
00:25:37,368 --> 00:25:39,233
Amen.

240
00:25:55,886 --> 00:25:59,583
- Excuse me. Is this Caroline Gill's?
- 3B? Yeah.

241
00:25:59,757 --> 00:26:02,351
